div1.p:
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Juducial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King.
HABEAS CORPUS.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting: We command you, that you have the body of William L. Tobias known in committment as William J. Tobias by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment adnd etention, by whatsoever name said William L. Tobias shall be called or charged, before the HON. C H Hanford Richard A. Jones, Judge of the aforesaid Court at One O'clock P. M. on the 28th day of Sept 1889 to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the said William L Tobias And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON.Richard A. Jones C H Hanford Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof tjis 28th day of Sept A. D. 1889. R M Hopkins Clerk. By Deputy Clerk.

No. 7255 In the District Court, Third Judicial District, Holding Terms at Seattle, W. T.
In the Matter of the Application of Wm.. L. Tobias For Writ of Habeas Corpus.
HABEAS CORPUS.
Returned and filed this 28 day of Sept A. D. 1889 R M Hopkins Clerk. By H. T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.
